# Zengin Format

## Record Structure (120 bytes, Shift_JIS)

Each data record is exactly 120 bytes. Fields are fixed-length, space-padded
or zero-padded depending on type:

| Field | Position | Length | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 種別コード (shorui) | 1 | 2 | numeric | `'11'`=給与, `'12'`=賞与 |
| 銀行コード | 3 | 4 | numeric | 4-digit bank code |
| 銀行名 | 7 | 15 | half-width kana | |
| 支店コード | 22 | 3 | numeric | |
| 支店名 | 25 | 15 | half-width kana | |
| 預金種別 | 40 | 1 | numeric | 1=普通, 2=当座, 4=貯蓄 |
| 口座番号 | 41 | 7 | numeric | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 受取人名 | 48 | 30 | half-width kana | |
| 振込金額 | 78 | 10 | numeric | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 新規コード | 88 | 1 | numeric | 1=初回, 2=変更, 0=その他 |
| EDI情報 | 89 | 20 | alphanumeric | optional, space-padded |
| 振込区分 | 109 | 1 | numeric | 7=電信, 9=文書 |
| ダミー | 110 | 11 | space-padded | all spaces |

## Shorui (種別コード) — LOAD-BEARING Type

```typescript
type ZenginShorui = '11' | '12';
```

- `'11'` = 給与振込 (payroll)
- `'12'` = 賞与振込 (bonus)
- NEVER widen to `string`
- NEVER accept `'21'` or any other code

## Half-Width Kana Conversion

All text fields require half-width katakana (半角カナ). Use the built-in
`toHalfWidthKana(text: string): string` converter which handles:
- Full-width → half-width conversion
- Voiced consonants (dakuten): ガ → ｶﾞ (2 chars)
- Semi-voiced (handakuten): パ → ﾊﾟ (2 chars)
- Length validation after conversion (field overflow = error, not truncation)

## Multi-bank Readiness

This package must NEVER contain GMO-specific defaults. See `packages/zengin-format/AGENTS.md`.

Bank info is always caller-provided:
```typescript
// ✅ Correct
generateZenginFile({ sourceBank: { code: '0310', nameKana: 'ｼﾞｰｴﾑｵｰｱｵｿﾞﾗ' }, ... });

// ❌ Wrong — hardcoded bank code
```

Before adding any new exported function, verify it works generically for
SMBC, MUFG, and regional banks (invoke `@multi-bank` if unsure).

## Control Records

- Header record (1 per file): total record count, file date, shorui code
- Trailer record (1 per file): total amount, data record count
- Counts in header/trailer must exactly match the data record array length

## Test Fixtures

Golden tests compare byte-exact output:

```typescript
expect(result.buffer).toEqual(expected); // ✅ Buffer equality
// ❌ never: toMatchSnapshot() — encoding-dependent
```

Fixture files in `fixtures/{bank}-sample-{purpose}.dat`. Each fixture file
must cite the source PDF URL in a header comment.

